## Dimension: Groundedness (HARD CONSTRAINT)

**Definition**: The degree to which every extracted claim is anchored to verbatim textual evidence from source responses.

**Why This Matters**: This is a hard constraint for validity. Without verifiable grounding, the graph cannot support transparent scientific advice. Every claim must be traceable to source text.

